# Python Package Architecture

## Core Package Structure
The main package is located at [agoras/](mdc:agoras) with the following key modules:

### API Layer
- [agoras/core/api/](mdc:agoras/core/api): Main API module containing platform integrations
- [agoras/core/api/auth/](mdc:agoras/core/api/auth): Authentication modules for each platform
- [agoras/core/api/clients/](mdc:agoras/core/api/clients): Client implementations for each platform

### Supported Platforms
The project supports multiple social media and communication platforms:
- **Discord**: [agoras/core/discord.py](mdc:agoras/core/discord.py) and [agoras/core/api/discord.py](mdc:agoras/core/api/discord.py)
- **Facebook**: [agoras/core/facebook.py](mdc:agoras/core/facebook.py) and [agoras/core/api/facebook.py](mdc:agoras/core/api/facebook.py)
- **Instagram**: [agoras/core/instagram.py](mdc:agoras/core/instagram.py) and [agoras/core/api/instagram.py](mdc:agoras/core/api/instagram.py)
- **LinkedIn**: [agoras/core/linkedin.py](mdc:agoras/core/linkedin.py) and [agoras/core/api/linkedin.py](mdc:agoras/core/api/linkedin.py)
- **TikTok**: [agoras/core/tiktok.py](mdc:agoras/core/tiktok.py) and [agoras/core/api/tiktok.py](mdc:agoras/core/api/tiktok.py)
- **Twitter**: [agoras/core/twitter.py](mdc:agoras/core/twitter.py) and [agoras/core/api/twitter.py](mdc:agoras/core/api/twitter.py)
- **YouTube**: [agoras/core/youtube.py](mdc:agoras/core/youtube.py) and [agoras/core/api/youtube.py](mdc:agoras/core/api/youtube.py)

### Core Functionality Modules
- [agoras/core/feed/](mdc:agoras/core/feed): RSS feed management and processing
- [agoras/core/media/](mdc:agoras/core/media): Media file handling (images, videos)
- [agoras/core/sheet/](mdc:agoras/core/sheet): Google Sheets integration for scheduling
- [agoras/core/base.py](mdc:agoras/core/base.py): Base classes and common functionality
- [agoras/core/utils.py](mdc:agoras/core/utils.py): Utility functions
- [agoras/core/logger.py](mdc:agoras/core/logger.py): Logging configuration

### CLI Interface
- [agoras/cli.py](mdc:agoras/cli.py): Command-line interface entry point
- [agoras/commands/](mdc:agoras/commands): CLI command implementations

## Architecture Patterns
- Each platform has separate core module and API module
- Authentication is centralized in the auth/ directory
- Client implementations are separated from core logic
- Media handling is abstracted through factory pattern
- Feed management supports scheduling and batch operations

## Testing
- Test files are located in [tests/](mdc:tests)
- Integration tests available as shell scripts: [test-post.sh](mdc:test-post.sh), [test-schedule.sh](mdc:test-schedule.sh), etc.
